  "text": "Other recorded variables included: 1. The number of cases receiving tramadol. 2. Time to recovery of spontaneous breathing. 3. Time to extubation: defined as the time interval between stopping dexmedetomidine or propofol and the fulfillment of extubation criteria. 4. Time to discharge from PACU. 5. Ramsay sedation scores [CITATION_1] were assessed at T2 and Rass agitation scores (RASS) [CITATION_2] were assessed at T3. At T3, if RASS score was at least 3 points, the patients were treated with analgesics (tramadol) and sedatives (dexmedetomidine or/and propofol with an infusion pump). Sedatives were continued for 30 min and then discontinued to awaken the patients. The RASS score was assessed for the second time. If RASS score was at least 3, the sedation was continued as before until RASS score was 2 or less. If RASS score was 2 or less, sedatives were discontinued and the patients regained consciousness gradually. 6. Cough responses during extubation were scored as 1=no",
